text:
Hey Everyone! It’s finally here! There will be companies with full-time and internship opportunities at this networking event today Oct 24th at 6pm in the Hinckley Building East Conference room. We are inviting all past MBA SCA Alumni and friends of the program that what to see BYU MBA's get into strategy or consulting roles!

Consulting Companies committed: *McKinsey, Bain, PwC, Slalom, Cicero, Clozd* (looking to get more to come)
Strategy Roles/Companies Committed: *Bill, Dees Limited, School Leadership Alliance, Henry Schein One, Security Metrics, BYU TV* (looking to get more to come)

If you are interested in Consulting it will be a great opportunity!

If you are interested in Strategic roles or strategy roles this will be a great opportunity!

*Many of these companies are looking for interns and full-time roles or have connections to opportunities!*

There will be a soda bar and Hors d'oeuvres
*NOW FREE for everyone - we have decided to drop the fee (thank you, anonymous supporter)*
Business Casual

:large_blue_diamond: *Important* Blue Lounge Updates for <!channel> :large_blue_diamond:

1. We will be changing the door code to the MBA lounge this week on *Friday morning.* The *new door code will be 20234* (think of the school year 2023-24). We know that the mid-year change is a pain and tried to hold off on changing it, but the existing code is pretty broadly known outside the MBA and we've had multiple issues of non-MBAs spending time here late in the evening/on the weekends and want to keep things locked and safe.
2. A huge THANK YOU to <@U03PKR5GQUQ> and her helper <@U03LMGSGBQC> for decorating the lounge for us - it looks amazing!!

:rotating_light: BETA COURSE TEST AUDIENCE NEEDED :rotating_light:<!channel>

Hi Friends, I have a HUGE favor to ask!

I'm currently building out a _*Intro to Total Rewards*_ course for my business and need some volunteers to serve as "beta testers". All you need to do is show up to my presentation on *Friday, November 3rd from 12:30-2:30pm,* ask any questions you may have about Total Rewards, and provide me with some feedback via a survey link I'll send out after the class.

I'm hoping to get _at least_ 20 attendees - both 1st and 2nd years - and will bribe you with treats! :slightly_smiling_face: If you have any specific questions about Total Rewards that you would like me to talk about, shoot me a DM!

I'm testing out a function on my website (please don't review the website...it's currently in a pathetic state of despair :tired_face:) and would LOVE if you would reserve a seat through this link: <https://millennialhrgal.com/ola/services/beta-course-intro-to-total-rewards-byu-mba-audience>

Thank you, thank you, thank you!!! :two_hearts:
-Ashlee
